The paper deals with the problem of quantized compressive sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the restricted isometry property (RIP), which is a topic in linear algebra and optimization (cs.LG). The paper presents a signal reconstruction method, which involves low-rank matrices (cs.MM) and sparse signals (cs.NA).
